Partitional clustering¶

In [6]:
# K-means (sklearn.cluster.KMeans)

from sklearn import cluster
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
%matplotlib inline

X = data.iloc[0:178,1:14]
y = pd.DataFrame(data['Class'])

def KmeansPlot(X,y,title,px_idx=0,py_idx=1):
  plt.figure(figsize=(3, 3))
  plt.scatter(X.iloc[:, px_idx], X.iloc[:, py_idx], c=y)
  plt.title(title, fontsize=16, color="grey")

  km2 = cluster.KMeans(n_clusters=2).fit(X)
  km3 = cluster.KMeans(n_clusters=3).fit(X)
  km4 = cluster.KMeans(n_clusters=4).fit(X)

  plt.figure(figsize=(9, 3))
  plt.subplot(131)
  plt.scatter(X.iloc[:, px_idx], X.iloc[:, py_idx], c=km2.labels_)
  plt.title("K=2, J=%.2f" % km2.inertia_)
  #inertia_:sum of squared distances of samples to their closest cluster center

  plt.subplot(132)
  plt.scatter(X.iloc[:, px_idx], X.iloc[:, py_idx], c=km3.labels_)
  plt.title("K=3, J=%.2f" % km3.inertia_)

  plt.subplot(133)
  plt.scatter(X.iloc[:, px_idx], X.iloc[:, py_idx], c=km4.labels_)
  plt.title("K=4, J=%.2f" % km4.inertia_)

1. 比較使用原始資料所有features，和只使用 alcohol與malic acid的分群結果¶

In [9]:
# Fit all features of original data
KmeansPlot(X,y['Class'],'1. Fit all features of original data')
# Fit only alcohol and malic acid
X_2 = X.iloc[:,:2]
KmeansPlot(X_2,y['Class'],'2. Fit only alcohol and malic acid (x=alcohol, y=malic acid)')
看起來使用所有 features並分成三群的結果，和資料原來的分群最為相似。¶
J代表inertia，inertia的算法為樣本點到最近的群中心的距離平方和，所以分越多群 J值就越小。¶

2. 比較使用原始資料，和使用標準化後的原始資料的分群結果。¶

In [10]:
# Fit all features of original data
KmeansPlot(X,y['Class'],'Fit all features of original data')
# Fit all features of normalized data
X_normal = (X-X.mean())/X.std()
KmeansPlot(X_normal,y['Class'],'Fit all features of normalized data')
看起來使用標準化後的資料並分成三群的結果，和資料原來的分群非常相似，只有少數幾個點不一樣。¶
進行標準化處理，是為了避免每個 feature因為單位不同，導致在距離的計算上失真。¶

該如何決定分群的最佳數目?¶

可以利用 Elbow Method 或 Average Silhouette Method¶

In [13]:
# K-Means Elbow Method
distortions = []
for k in range(2,10):
  kmeanModel = cluster.KMeans(n_clusters=k).fit(X_normal)
  distortions.append(kmeanModel.inertia_)

plt.figure(figsize=(8,4))
plt.plot(range(2,10), distortions, 'bx-')
plt.axvline(x=3, c='r', ls='-.')
plt.xlabel('K number')
plt.ylabel('Distortion')
plt.title('Elbow Method')
Out[13]:
Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Elbow Method')
從 Elbow Method的結果可以看出，位於轉折處的 K number為 3，所以 Elbow Method 認為分成 3群最合適。¶
In [14]:
# K-Means Average Silhouette Method
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score

silhouette_avg = []
for k in range(2,11):
  kmeanModel = cluster.KMeans(n_clusters=k).fit(X_normal)
  silhouette_avg.append(silhouette_score(X_normal, kmeanModel.labels_))

plt.figure(figsize=(8,4))
plt.plot(range(2,11), silhouette_avg)
plt.axvline(x=3, c='r', ls='-.')
plt.xlabel('K number')
plt.ylabel('Silhouette score')
plt.title('Average Silhouette Method')
Out[14]:
Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Average Silhouette Method')
從 Average Silhouette Method的結果可以看出，擁有最高分的Silhouette score的 K number為 3，所以 Average Silhouette Method 也是認為分成 3群最合適。¶

def KmedoidsPlot(X,y,title,px_idx=0,py_idx=1):
  plt.figure(figsize=(3, 3))
  plt.scatter(X.iloc[:, px_idx], X.iloc[:, py_idx], c=y)
  plt.title(title, fontsize=16, color="grey")

  km3 = cluster.KMeans(n_clusters=3).fit(X)
  kmd3 = KMedoids(n_clusters=3).fit(X)

  plt.figure(figsize=(6, 3))
    
  plt.subplot(121)
  plt.scatter(X.iloc[:, px_idx], X.iloc[:, py_idx], c=km3.labels_)
  plt.title("Kmeans, K=3, J=%.2f" % km3.inertia_)

  plt.subplot(122)
  plt.scatter(X.iloc[:, px_idx], X.iloc[:, py_idx], c=kmd3.labels_)
  plt.title("Kmedoids, K=3, J=%.2f" % kmd3.inertia_)

Hierarchical clustering¶

linkage method: 'single' (最近距離)，'complete' (最遠距離), 'average'(平均距離), 'centroid' (中心點距離), 'ward' (群內變異最小)¶
In [25]:
# Hierarchical clustering: bottom-up
from scipy.cluster.hierarchy import dendrogram,linkage,fcluster

A = linkage(X_normal, 'single') #construct linkage matrix
B = linkage(X_normal, 'complete')
C = linkage(X_normal, 'average')
D = linkage(X_normal, 'centroid')
E = linkage(X_normal, 'ward')

A_clu = fcluster(A,t=3,criterion='maxclust') #assign max cluster number
print(A_clu)
B_clu = fcluster(B,t=3,criterion='maxclust') 
print(B_clu)
C_clu = fcluster(C,t=3,criterion='maxclust') 
print(C_clu)
D_clu = fcluster(D,t=3,criterion='maxclust') 
print(D_clu)
E_clu = fcluster(E,t=3,criterion='maxclust') 
print(E_clu)

Partitional Clustering : 需指定分群數目，只能分成大群，但執行速度很快。¶
Hierarchical Clustering : 不需指定分群數目，可以分得較細，但較費時。¶
